news.title: Delhi civic body will put Bhalswa Dairy colony's demolition drive on hold till August 16
news.para: In July, the court had directed the authorities to ensure that unauthorised construction in all dairy colonies in the national capital is removed and asked them to take immediate steps for shifting dairies from Bhalswa to Ghogha dairy colony within four weeks.

news.title: Sweden's Oscar Properties reaches deal with creditor to avoid bankruptcy
news.para: The creditor, housing association Innovationen, owner of a residential tower in Stockholm that Oscar Properties developed, requested last month that the company be declared bankrupt over unpaid claims of around 15 million crowns ($1.4 million).

news.title: Government issues guidelines for model solar village
news.para: A financial outlay of Rs 800 crore has been allocated for this component, providing Rs 1 crore per selected Model Solar Village, the ministry said.

news.title: Berger Paints eyes 5% value growth in Q2 FY25
news.para: Berger Paints said that its next milestone is to double its turnover to Rs 20,000 crore by 2029, up from Rs 10,000 crore in FY2024.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates seeks interim relief from NCLAT
news.para: The Allahabad bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) in June ordered initiation of corporate insolvency resolution process (CIRP) against JAL, on a complaint by ICICI Bank that accused the construction and infrastructure company of defaulting on payment of Rs 1,269 crore.

news.title: Max Estates receives Noida authority's approval to overtake ‘Delhi One’ project, to pay Rs 613 crore
news.para: In February 2023, the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) approved the resolution plan of Max for the development of a commercial plot measuring 34,697 square meters in Noida under the project name ‘Delhi One’.

news.title: RBI reviews regulations applicable to housing finance companies
news.para: RBI has announced changes on minimum percentage of liquid assets, which specifies that all deposit taking housing finance companies shall maintain liquid assets to the extent of 15 per cent of the public deposits as against 13 per cent right now.

news.title: RBI penalises Muthoot Housing Finance, Nido Home Finance, others
news.para: A fine of 5 lakh has been imposed on Muthoot Housing Finance Company for non-compliance with certain provisions of the 'Non-Banking Financial Company - Housing Finance Company (Reserve Bank) Directions, 2021', the central bank said in another release.

news.title: NBCC to develop two land parcels worth Rs 710 crore in Jhansi
news.para: The company will develop two land parcels including an approximately 12.28 acre land on Jhansi-Kanpur Highway and another land parcel of about 1.07 acre in the medical compound, college road, Kanpur Road.

news.title: Hy-Vee leases 54,000 sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: It has over 550 retail business units across the United States and generates nearly $14 billion in annual sales.

news.title: hBits launches Rs 62.97 crore fractional ownership asset in Pune
news.para: It spans across a chargeable area of 40,000 sq ft. The rental inflow and purchase price of the asset offers an entry yield of 8.75% and an expected internal rate of return of 14.53%.

news.title: Hindenburg Research claims baseless, misleading: Indian REITs Association
news.para: Brookfield India Real Estate Trust, Embassy Office Parks REIT, Mindspace Business Parks REIT, and Nexus Select Trust are the founding members of the Indian REITs Association.

news.title: Axis AMC & Tishman Speyer acquires 1.5 acres plot in Fintech City, Chennai
news.para: The acquisition was made through a bid cum e-auction process conducted by the Tamil Nadu Industrial Development Corporation (TIDCO).

news.title: REA India's revenue rises 31% to Rs 563 crore in FY24
news.para: Commenting on the performance, Agarwala said, "FY24 has been a year of significant growth and innovation for our company. The success of our online events, which achieved record collections, reflects our strong market presence and the effectiveness of our strategy."

news.title: Commercial property prices in Germany drop 7.4% in Q2 2024
news.para: The values of commercial real estate - in decline for two years - showed a 0.4% rise from the first three months of this year, in a sign of the market "calming down", VDP said.

news.title: Hong Kong court gives Kaisa Group more time to restructure debt
news.para: A Hong Kong court on Monday gave troubled Chinese developer Kaisa four more weeks to work with bondholders to come up with a viable restructuring plan. Shenzhen-based Kaisa is the second-largest issuer of offshore bonds among Chinese developers, behind Evergrande, and first defaulted on its debt in 2021.

news.title: Bengaluru: Anjanapura BDA Layout residents rejects slum relocation
news.para: The situation changed when the Karnataka Slum Development Board decided to relocate slum dwellers from Kengeri and Shankarpally to Anjanapura, instead of the initially planned Uttarahalli and Gollahalli. Due to strong opposition from Gollahalli residents, the relocation site was moved to Kembathalli Village near NICE Road.

news.title: Cement companies reports volume growth in Q1 FY25
news.para: Major cement companies in India reported slight volume growth in the June quarter amid falling prices and higher raw material costs. UltraTech, Ambuja Cements, and ACC saw increased sales and capacity utilization. Nonetheless, overall revenue growth was limited, and construction activities slowed due to intense heatwaves and elections, hurting profits.

news.title: Bengaluru: Whitefield residents express concerns over PG accommodation guidelines
news.para: ​There is widespread dissatisfaction with the BBMP’s regulation of the PG business, and residents feel that more comprehensive measures are required.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 90 acres of land in Khalapur, Maharashtra
news.para: The land is located near Karjat Khopoli Road and is estimated to have a development potential of approximately 1.7 million sq ft of saleable area comprising primarily of residential plotted development.
